## Your job

You decide what changes the LoreLake wiki needs to reflect the code changes in
{{COMMIT_RANGE}}. You do NOT write any wiki files. You emit a single JSON
"plan" that a Python applier will execute deterministically.

Your final assistant message must be exactly one JSON document and nothing else
— no prose around it, no Markdown fences. The plan format is below.

## Inputs you have

A pre-built context directory exists at:

    {{CONTEXT_DIR}}

It contains:
- `changes.json` — per-commit metadata and the union list of changed files.
- `diffs/<safe-name>.patch` — per-file unified diffs. Large files are split
  into `<safe-name>.001.patch`, `.002.patch`, … with `<safe-name>.index.json`
  listing the chunks. Use `Glob` and `Read` to inspect them.
- `wiki-index.json` — flat catalog of every wiki page (slug → frontmatter
  fields and path). Use this to know what pages exist before deciding to
  create new ones.

You may also Read existing wiki pages under {{WIKI_ROOT}}/ when you need their
current content to compose surgical edits.

